        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(policy): reject unsupported policy keys",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis is the next stacked Policy follow-up after #87056. It brings policy file shape validation to the same strict bar as the sandbox posture work:\n\n- rejects unsupported top-level policy sections instead of ignoring them\n- rejects unsupported nested rule keys across channels, MCP, models, network, ingress, Gateway, agents, tools, sandbox, secrets, auth profiles, and data-handling policy\n- documents that unsupported sections or rule keys report `policy/policy-jsonc-invalid`\n\nThis is config/policy validation only. It does not add runtime enforcement.\n\n## Stack note\n\nThis branch is currently opened against `main` for GitHub visibility, but the reviewable change is the final commit:\n\n- `c6b6696f2c6 fix(policy): reject unsupported policy keys`\n\nIt is stacked after the active policy line, including #85572, #85744, #86768, and #87056.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts docs/cli/policy.md`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-policy-shape7 OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/cli.test.ts -- --reporter=dot --testTimeout=30000`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx docs/cli/policy.md`\n- `node scripts/run-bundled-extension-oxlint.mjs`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `~/.codex/skills/codex-review/scripts/codex-review --mode local`\n\n",
